<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<section xml:id="section-1" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Creating the First Program</title>
  
  <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li><p>Startup the p5.js editor and properly log in</p></li>
      <li><p>Run the starter code</p></li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>

  <p>
    The p5.js editor is where we will write, save, and run our JavaScript programs. We will 
    use some elements from the p5.js library to make our programs visual, which can help us  
    <q>see</q> whether or not our program is doing what we want it to do. The visual components
    also make programs both interesting and fun!
  </p>

  <p>Let's get started!</p>

  <p>
    Open the editor in your browser: <url href="https://editor.p5js.org/"/> or you can search 
    for <alert>"p5js editor"</alert>
  </p>

  <p>
    To enlarge any image, click once on the image. Click again to make it normal size.
  </p>
 
  <figure xml:id="new-editor">
    <caption>A new editor, with a code window containing <alert>starter code</alert></caption>
    <image source="images/NewEditor.png" width="80%"/>    
  </figure>

  <p>Choose <alert>Log in</alert> in the upper-right corner and a window, like the one below, will appear.</p>
  
  <figure xml:id="login-screen">
    <caption>Select, Login with Google using your CA account.</caption>
    <image source="images/LoginScreen.png" width="40%"/>    
  </figure>

  <p>Press the <alert>Play</alert> button.</p>
  
  <figure xml:id="fig-blank-canvas">
    <caption>Creates a blank canvas, which is the gray square to the right of the code window.</caption>
    <image source="images/NewEditorRun.png" width="80%"/>    
  </figure>

  <p>
    Although they are too tiny to see, the default canvas is made up of 160,000 (400x400) dots 
    called <term>Pixels</term>. We will explore pixels more in the following sections.
  </p>

  <p>
    <em>NOTE:</em> We will often use <term>js</term> for JavaScript and <term>p5</term> for either the p5.js 
    editor or library.
  </p>   
</section>